## Vercel Web Analytics Integration

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the Smart Traffic Intelligence project.

### Changes Made

**1. Installed Package:**
- Added `@vercel/analytics` version 2.0.1 to project dependencies
- Used `npm install @vercel/analytics --legacy-peer-deps` to resolve peer dependency conflicts

**2. Updated Files:**

**frontend/app/layout.tsx:**
- Imported `Analytics` component from `@vercel/analytics/next`
- Added `<Analytics />` component at the end of the `<body>` tag in the RootLayout component
- Follows Next.js App Router best practices by placing analytics in the root layout

**frontend/package.json:**
- Added `@vercel/analytics: ^2.0.1` to dependencies

**frontend/package-lock.json:**
- Updated with new package dependencies (automatically handled by npm)

### Implementation Details

The implementation follows the official Vercel Analytics documentation for Next.js App Router:
- Retrieved latest documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart
- Placed the Analytics component in the root layout file as recommended
- The component is positioned at the end of the body, after the main content
- This ensures analytics tracking is loaded on all pages of the application

### Verification

All verification steps passed successfully:
✅ Build completed without errors (`npm run build`)
✅ Linter passed with no issues (`npm run lint`)
✅ All tests passed (6/6 tests) (`npm run test`)
✅ TypeScript compilation successful

### Next Steps

To complete the setup:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel
2. Navigate to Analytics in the Vercel dashboard and click "Enable"
3. After deployment, verify tracking is active by checking the browser Network tab for `/_vercel/insights/*` requests
4. Access the analytics dashboard to view collected data

The Analytics component will automatically track page views and user interactions once deployed to Vercel's platform.
